[4] Cholera - Angola (Namibe)
Date: Fri, 17 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=488478>

Around 16 cases of cholera were registered between 12 to 15 Nov 2006, in
the municipality of Tombwa, located 93 kilometres south of Namibe city,
said Thu, 16 Nov 2006 to ANGOP the clinical director of the local hospital,
Joao Campos.
According to the official, in the registered cases there were no deaths,
all the patients are being treated and preventive measures are being taken
to put an end to the epidemics.
