[5] Cholera - Angola (Benguela)
Date: Mon, 13 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=487440>

Three people died of cholera in Bumbwa village in Caimbambo municipality,
southwestern Benguela Province, announced Sat, 11 Nov 2006, the local
administrator, Lucas Roque.
According to the source, in the mentioned period 32 cases were recorded in
that district.
