[6] Cholera - Angola (Cunene)
Date: Mon, 13 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=487534>

A total of 21 people died of cholera in Angola's southern Cunene province's
districts of Kwanhama, Kahama and Cuvelai, last week. The information was
released by Cunene provincial health director, Eduardo Haiumba, who added
about 300 cases have so far been reported in those 3 districts.
