[7] Cholera - Angola (Huila)
Date: Sat, 11 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=487122>

At least 62 new cholera cases were registered in the last 24 hours by
Huila health authorities, in Lubango and Quipungo municipalities, killing
one person.
The fact was revealed to ANGOP by the acting public health department
chief, Felix Januario, adding that from these cases, 61 occurred in
Lubango, killing one person and one nonfatal case in Quipungo district.
According to Felix Januario, currently 102 patients are hospitalized in
"Doutor Agostinho Neto" Central Hospital, while other 106 were discharged
on the same period.
Since the start of cholera outbreak in Apr 2006 in Huila, a total of 1891
cases were registered, thus claiming 122 lives.
--
